channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Iran's President Raisi killed in helicopter crash
item.description: Iran's President Ebrahim Raisi has died in a helicopter crash, the government has confirmed. Follow for live updates

item.title: Georgia's parliament speaker vows to override presidential veto on divisive law
item.description: Georgia’s parliament speaker on Monday vowed to override a presidential veto on divisive legislation that sparked weeks of mass protests by critics who see it as a threat to democratic freedoms and the country’s aspirations to join the European Union

item.title: Devastation in Gaza as Israel wages war on Hamas
item.description: Israeli war cabinet divisions broke into the open over the weekend when member Benny Gantz demanded the cabinet lay out a plan for the war against Hamas by June 8, threatening to otherwise withdraw from the government. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Iran's President Raisi dead in helicopter crash, Iranian state media reports
item.description: Iran's President Ebrahim Raisi is dead following a helicopter crash, Iranian state media announced Monday morning local time.

item.title: May 19, 2024 helicopter crash involving Iranian president
item.description: A helicopter carrying Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi crashed while he was visiting a northern region in the country Sunday, according to the Iranian state news agency IRNA.

item.title: London court to decide whether WikiLeaks founder Assange is extradited to the US
item.description: WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange faces a court hearing in London that could end with him being sent to the U.S. to face espionage charges, or provide him another chance to appeal his extradition

item.title: May 19, 2024 - Israel-Gaza news
item.description: An Israeli airstrike on a refugee camp in central Gaza has killed at least 35 people, including seven children, according to hospital officials. Meanwhile, Israeli war cabinet divisions are spilling into the open.

item.title: Senior Republican criticizes Biden in speech to Israeli parliament
item.description: Stefanik is seen as a candidate to be Donald Trump’s running mate.

item.title: Many remember solid economy under Trump, but his record also full of hype, debt
item.description: Numbers show that the economy during Donald Trump’s presidency has never lived up to his own hype
